  "response": "To reset your Gmail password, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the Gmail sign-in page\n\n2. Click on \"Forgot password?\"\n\n3. Google will ask you to verify your identity:\n- Enter your email address\n- Choose a verification method (phone, backup email, etc.)\n\n4. Follow the verification steps:\n- If using phone: Enter the code sent to your phone\n- If using backup email: Check your alternate email for a verification code\n- Answer security questions (if applicable)\n\n5. Once verified, create a new password:\n- Choose a strong, unique password\n- Make sure it's different from previous passwords\n- Use a mix of letters, numbers, and symbols\n\n6. After setting the new password, sign in to your account\n\nTips:\n- Ensure you have a recovery email and phone number set up\n- Use a password manager for added security\n- Don't use easily guessable passwords\n\nIf you're having trouble, visit the Google Account recovery page or contact Google support.",
